### "Legal gun ownership and homicides in Brazil" 

------------------------------------------------------------------------

#### Synopsis:

This study uses Bayesian multilevel models to analyze the association between 
legal gun ownership and homicide rates in Brazil. It used official data on 
firearm possession and licenses to carry rather than proxy measures. The 
results suggest that legal gun ownership is unlikely to be a significant driver 
of homicide rates. Preprint available on [CrimRxiv](https://doi.org/10.21428/cb6ab371.b1300c2c){target="_blank"}. 

